---
description: DPMK/AUSEMIO integration rules
globs: backend/**,frontend/**
---

The application integrates with the existing DPMK/AUSEMIO public issue form.

External endpoint:
`https://kosice.ausemio.io/public_issues`

The endpoint must be configurable through environment variables.
Do not hardcode integration values across the codebase.

The request format is:
- HTTP method: POST
- Content-Type: multipart/form-data

Identified AUSEMIO/DPMK fields:
- properties[vyber_sluzby]
- properties[ulica_miesto_poruchy_lokalita]
- properties[detail_decription]
- properties[lokalizacia_blok]
- properties[typ_poruchy]
- properties[typ_poruchy_css]
- properties[porucha_na_prechode_pre_chodcov]
- properties[porucha_na_cestnej_svetelnej_signalizacii]
- properties[iny_druh_poruchy]
- properties[tel_cislo]
- files[]
- email
- locale

Important:
Keep the exact field name `properties[detail_decription]`.
Do not rename it to `description`, even though it looks like a typo.

Integration mapping must be centralized in one backend file, for example:
`backend/src/config/ausemioMapping.ts`

Service VO – verejné osvetlenie is supported.
CSS – cestná svetelná signalizácia is not part of the public application scope.

Attachments must be sent through `files[]`.

Success is evaluated according to the HTTP response from AUSEMIO/DPMK.

On error, show a clear user-friendly error message.

Do not automatically retry sending without the user's knowledge.

Before real production sending, keep a test mode.
Real production testing must happen only after approval from the city or system administrator.
